<div id="content" class="content wikipage" lang="en" dir="ltr">
<p id="l1">
In the metric system, series of standard paper sizes based on portions of a square meter. The basic paper sizes are known as the <a title="A Series" href="A_Series">A series</a>, and the B series comprises intermediate paper sizes to the A series. The length-to-width ratio is maintained from size to size. The metric standard size that corresponds most closely to the United States standard letter size of 8H x 11 is A4-size paper. (See <a title="A Series" href="A_Series">A Series</a> and <a title="ISO Paper Sizes" href="ISO_Paper_Sizes">ISO Paper Sizes</a>. See also <a title="Basis Weight" href="Basis_Weight">Basis Weight</a> and <a title="Grammage" href="Grammage">Grammage</a>.) The sizes and area of B series paper (from sizes B0 to B10) are as follows: [Insert] 
</p>
